  "informal_statement": "For every natural number n and every function f : nat -> nat such that f i > 0 for every i < n, the product of f over the range [0, n) is positive.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Induction on n. Base case n = 0: the empty product is 1, which is positive. Successor case: given ih for k and hf covering range (k+1), split off the last factor via Finset.prod_range_succ to get (prod over range k) * f k, then Nat.mul_pos combines positivity of the smaller product (from ih, restricting hf to range k via a strict-inequality-widening argument) with positivity of f k (from hf applied to k itself, which lies in range (k+1)).",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem prod_range_pos : ∀ (n : ℕ) (f : ℕ → ℕ), (∀ i ∈ Finset.range n, 0 < f i) → 0 < ∏ i ∈ Finset.range n, f i",
